  "text": "Due to the long wavelengths of the THz radiation (1 THz ↔ 0.3 mm), ΔT(f, t) is dominated by free carrier absorption which is proportional to the photo-induced conductivity Δσ = eµΔn consisting of the charge carrier mobility µ and concentration Δn 33 . Therefore, the measured THz transmission T and its photoinduced change ΔT can be used in equation [CITATION_1] to calculate the photo-induced conductivity as well as the mobility if the induced charge carrier concentration is known [CITATION_2] .",
